snippet.textDisplay: That's incredible that was such an amazing venue. I saw zebrahead  around the same era when Canes bar and grill still existed. For those who never got a chance to catch a show there, it was a small intimate venue. There where 2 floors, the top floor was just dedicated to drinking and dining and the bottom floor a small bar that gave the appearance of a dive bar, with the ocean just beyond the doors.  The bottom floor had a small area  with stage on one side and a bar acrooss from it. No matter where you stood you where right in the middle of the action. On the night that I saw zebrahead  I got to meet  all the original members and got drink and chat with them.  I would of love to have also seen Linkin Park around this era, if you guys remember this also when 311 soundsystem and from chaos was still Fresh  and zebraheads  waste of mind and playmate of year was also still relatively new.  Thanks for sharing.  In the year 2000 when I was in college  Hybrid Theory, Waste of Mind, and Soundsystem where in heavy rotation with me and my roomates.  Love you Chester!

snippet.textDisplay: So many emotions while watching this. Part of me wants to cry tears of joy at how amazing and beautiful these songs really are.  Another part of me is sad that Chester is no longer with us physically, and it's hard to believe, and also that we won't see anymore amazing albums like this. Chester was one hell of a front man. He could sing melodically,  scream like nobody's business, and do everything in between, and he was also full of energy and passion. One of the best front man ever in my opinion. Another part of me gets a fair amount of adrenaline where I feel like I could walk through a wall. The power and energy of the music just resonates so much with me.  One last thing before I stop rambling. I FUCKING LOVE YOU LP, YOU CHANGED MY LIFE AND HAVE GIVEN ME SO MANY GOOD TIMES AND MEMORIES. PEACE AND LOVE TO YOU ALL! :)
snippet.textOriginal: So many emotions while watching this. Part of me wants to cry tears of joy at how amazing and beautiful these songs really are.  Another part of me is sad that Chester is no longer with us physically, and it's hard to believe, and also that we won't see anymore amazing albums like this. Chester was one hell of a front man. He could sing melodically,  scream like nobody's business, and do everything in between, and he was also full of energy and passion. One of the best front man ever in my opinion. Another part of me gets a fair amount of adrenaline where I feel like I could walk through a wall. The power and energy of the music just resonates so much with me.  One last thing before I stop rambling. I FUCKING LOVE YOU LP, YOU CHANGED MY LIFE AND HAVE GIVEN ME SO MANY GOOD TIMES AND MEMORIES. PEACE AND LOVE TO YOU ALL! :)

snippet.textDisplay: I was 17 years old when I first heard your music and it came to me at the most perfect time it could. There had been a lot of hardships back then and your music just resonated with me. By 18 I had dyed blonde (group of us did a charity night where we all dressed as eminem and did a parody) after that I styled it like Chester's for a few months. Your music has always ment alot to me and many others. Just hate the fact I never got the opportunity to see you all live. My own fault as I made other things (alcohol and drugs) that I never should have a priority instead and that will always be a massive regret for me. Just want to say we love you all and thank you
